# Dependency-audit posture for deployment.
# Rationale + per-advisory triage: notes/npm-audit-residual-risk-2026-05.md
# High/critical are gated UPSTREAM by our security-safety review before anything ships.
# Moderate/low are triaged & accepted per that sign-off, so they must not block or alarm
# the university-admin build. (Our security agent runs `npm audit --json` explicitly and
# still sees every severity for triage — these settings only affect the build/install path.)

# No advisory summary during `npm install` / `npm ci`:
audit=false

# If an explicit `npm audit` / CI gate is run anyway, only high+ fails (moderate/low pass):
audit-level=high

# Quiet the funding nag during install:
fund=false
